# Khaao frontend — Firebase web app config (v3)
#
# Quick start: `cp .env.example .env`, fill in the four values below, then
# `npm run dev`. Vite only reads .env at server start — restart after edits.
#
# This file is a TEMPLATE (tracked in git) — never put real keys in it.
# Real values go in `.env` (gitignored, see the repo root .gitignore).
#
# ============================================================================
# HOW TO GET THESE VALUES — step by step
# ============================================================================
# All four come from the SAME screen, and it's the SAME Firebase project the
# backend's FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID points at (see backend/.env.example #1 first
# if you haven't created that project yet):
#
#   1. https://console.firebase.google.com → open your project
#   2. ⚙️ (gear icon, top-left) → "Project settings"
#   3. Scroll to "Your apps" → if there's no Web app (</> icon) yet, click
#      "Add app" → Web → give it any nickname (e.g. "khaao-web") → Register.
#      You do NOT need Firebase Hosting — skip that step if offered. Firebase
#      may also offer to set up Analytics; decline it, this app doesn't use it.
#   4. Firebase shows a `firebaseConfig` object right there (or under
#      Project settings → General → Your apps → SDK setup and configuration
#      if you already created the app earlier) — copy each field into the
#      matching variable below. Only these 4 fields are needed; ignore any
#      extra ones Firebase shows (storageBucket, messagingSenderId,
#      measurementId) — this app doesn't use Analytics/Storage:
#        apiKey        → VITE_FIREBASE_API_KEY
#        authDomain    → VITE_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN   (looks like <project>.firebaseapp.com)
#        projectId     → VITE_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID    (same value as the backend's FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID)
#        appId         → VITE_FIREBASE_APP_ID
#   5. Back in Authentication → Sign-in method, make sure "Google" is enabled
#      as a provider (same step noted in backend/.env.example) — without it
#      the "Continue with Google" button will fail with an auth/* error.
#   6. Before your real domain goes live: Authentication → Settings →
#      "Authorized domains" → add it. localhost is allowed by default, which
#      is why local dev works without this step.
#
# These four values are public client identifiers, not secrets — anyone can
# see them in browser devtools once the app is deployed. All real access
# control (student email domain, shopkeeper allowlist) happens on the
# backend, which independently re-verifies every Google ID token.
# ============================================================================

VITE_FIREBASE_API_KEY=
VITE_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=
VITE_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=
VITE_FIREBASE_APP_ID=
